    addNode(108, "RefPedia_presentation.txt", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "RefPedia — App Overview\n\nRefPedia is a mobile app (iOS & Android) for basketball referees to learn, practice, and test their skills in one place (videos, quizzes, camera exercises, exams).\n\nProblem: Traditional training is slow, rigid, and non-interactive.\nSolution: 5 integrated learning modules:\n\n📹 Video lessons (rules, fouls, signals)\n🎬 Video quiz (real game scenarios)\n✋ Hand signal recognition (image-based quiz)\n📷 Camera practice (perform signals)\n📝 Theoretical exam (practice or timed)\n\nKey Features:\n\nAuthentication (email, Google, Guest)\nUser profile + feedback\nIn-app notifications\nAdmin panel (content management)\nAI moderation (Gemini)\n\nUser Flow: Login/Signup/Guest → Home → learning & testing modules\n\nAudience: referees, instructors, basketball enthusiasts\nPlatforms: iOS & Android", 7);
    addNode(109, "RefPedia_documantation", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "RefPedia — Technical Overview\n\nTech Stack: React Native (Expo), Expo Router, Firebase (Auth, Firestore, Storage), Google Gemini API, expo-video/av, expo-camera, AsyncStorage\n\nArchitecture: Modular, component-based (UI, logic, services)\n\nApp: file-based screens (auth, learning, quizzes, profile)\nComponents: reusable UI\nServices: Firebase integration\nState: React Context\n\nCore Features:\n\nAuth (email + Google)\nLearning (video + quizzes)\nPractice (camera-based)\nExams (timed/tests)\nFeedback (AI moderation)\nNotifications\n\nDatabase (Firestore): users, enunturi, camera, feedback, messages\n\nSecurity: Auth, role-based access, AI moderation, Firebase rules\n\nDesign: Responsive UI, centralized theme, mobile-first UX", 7);
    addNode(110, "RefPedia_terms&conditions.txt", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "By using RefPedia, you agree to these terms.\nEffective / Last Updated: March 21, 2026\n\n1. Use of the App\nRefPedia is an educational tool for learning basketball refereeing. It is intended for personal, non-commercial use only. You agree to use the app responsibly and in accordance with applicable laws.\n\n2. Accounts & Access\nSome features require an account. You are responsible for keeping your login details secure. Guest mode offers limited access without registration.\n\n3. Content & Intellectual Property\nAll app content (videos, quizzes, design, etc.) is protected and may not be copied or reused without permission. Basketball rules themselves remain public domain.\n\n4. User Conduct\nYou agree not to misuse the app, attempt unauthorized access, or submit harmful, offensive, or irrelevant content.\n\n5. Data & Privacy\nWe collect minimal data (email, app usage, feedback). We do not collect sensitive data such as photos (stored locally only) or location data. Services like Firebase and Google Sign-In may process data according to their policies.\n\n6. Feedback & Moderation\nUser feedback may be moderated automatically. Inappropriate content may be removed.\n\n7. Disclaimer\nThe app is provided “as is” without guarantees of accuracy or availability. RefPedia does not provide official certification.\n\n8. Liability\nWe are not responsible for any damages resulting from the use of the app.\n\n9. Changes\nTerms may be updated at any time. Continued use means you accept the changes.\n\n10. Contact\nmihai.arisanu2006@gmail.com", 7);
