    addNode(114, "NightDrive_presentation.txt", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "NightDrive — App Overview\n\nNightDrive is a real-time, community-driven navigation app for night drivers and car enthusiasts, combining navigation, social features, and hazard reporting in a sleek dark UI.\n\nProblem: Traditional GPS apps lack interactivity, social features, and night-optimized design.\nSolution: Integrated navigation + community platform:\n\n🌙 Night-mode navigation (dark UI, live GPS, speed, heading)\n🧭 Smart routing (turn-by-turn, dead reckoning, auto-reroute)\n⚠️ Real-time hazard reporting (community-verified)\n👥 Social system (hex tags, friends, messaging)\n🔐 Secure auth (JWT, Bcrypt)\n⭐ Saved places & route preferences\n\nDesign: OLED-dark, minimalist, neon-accented, distraction-free\n\nUser Flow: Login/Register → Map → Menu (profile, friends, saved, events)\n\nTech: React Native + Go + PostgreSQL/PostGIS + WebSockets + Docker\n\nWhy it stands out:\n\nNight-optimized UI\nActive community reporting\nWorks during GPS loss\nUnique identity system (hex tags)\nCustom route preferences\n\nTarget users: night drivers, commuters, car enthusiasts\n\nFuture: friend tracking, group drives, leaderboards, voice alerts, AI road scoring\n\nTagline: Navigate the night. Own the road. 🌙", 8);
    addNode(115, "NightDrive_documentation", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "NightDrive — Technical Overview\n\nNightDrive is a real-time, community-driven night navigation app built with React Native, Go, and PostgreSQL/PostGIS, focused on navigation, social features, and hazard reporting.\n\nArchitecture:\nMonorepo with 3 services (Docker Compose):\nClient (React Native) ↔ Backend (Go API) ↔ Database (PostgreSQL + PostGIS)\nCommunication: REST + WebSocket (real-time)\n\nTech Stack:\n\nClient: React Native (TypeScript), Google Maps, AsyncStorage\nBackend: Go, JWT auth, Bcrypt\nDatabase: PostgreSQL + PostGIS\nDeployment: Docker Compose\n\nCore Features:\n\nGPS tracking + dead reckoning + auto-rerouting\nEvent reporting (accidents, police, hazards, roadworks)\nCommunity voting & auto-expiration\nSocial system (friend tags, requests)\nAuthentication (JWT, secure passwords)\n\nBackend:\nEndpoints for users, events, friends, WebSocket updates\n\nDatabase:\nUsers, events, friendships, friend requests, saved routes\n\nDeployment:\nDockerized (frontend, backend, DB)\nRun with: docker-compose up --build\n\nConfig:\nEnv vars for API, Google Maps key, and database credentials", 8);
    addNode(116, "NightDrive_terms&conditions.txt", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "NightDrive — Terms & Conditions\n\nEffective / Last Updated: March 21, 2026\n\nNightDrive is a community-driven navigation app for car enthusiasts, providing real-time GPS navigation, social features, and crowd-sourced road event reporting. By using the App, users agree to comply with these Terms.\n\n1. User Eligibility & Accounts\nMust be ≥18 years old or legal driving age.\nValid driver’s license required if using while driving.\nAccount creation requires email, username, password, and generates a unique driver tag (e.g., #4Z9C).\nUsers are responsible for account security. Account deletion permanently removes data and friend connections.\n2. Acceptable Use\n\nUsers must:\n\nFollow traffic laws and report accurate road events.\nTreat other users respectfully.\n\nProhibited activities:\n\nUnsafe interaction while driving.\nFalse reports or vote manipulation.\nUnauthorized access, impersonation, or automated scraping.\n3. Driving Safety Disclaimer\nNightDrive is informational only; the driver is always responsible.\nGPS, dead reckoning, and community reports may contain errors.\nDo not use App features as a substitute for vehicle instruments.\nNightDrive and affiliates are not liable for accidents, fines, or damages.\n4. Community Content\nUsers are responsible for accuracy and legality of reports.\nEvent upvote/downvote system helps validate content but is not guaranteed.\nNightDrive may remove content violating Terms.\n5. Intellectual Property & Licensing\nApp code, design, logos, and brand are owned by NightDrive.\nLimited, personal-use license granted to users.\nThird-party services (Google Maps, PostGIS) are subject to their own terms.\n6. Privacy & Data\n\nCollected Data:\n\nAccount (email, username, tag, password hash)\nLocation (GPS) during active navigation\nUsage data (events, votes, friends, saved places)\nDevice info\n\nUsage: To provide navigation, social, and event features.\n\nSecurity:\n\nPasswords hashed via bcrypt\nAPI calls secured with JWT tokens\nEncrypted transmission\n\nSharing: Only with law enforcement, legal process, or essential service providers.\n\nUser Rights: Access, correct, delete, export data; withdraw consent at any time.\n\n7. Liability & Indemnification\nApp is provided “as is”; no warranties.\nNightDrive not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages.\nUsers indemnify NightDrive for claims arising from misuse or illegal activity.\n8. Termination\nUsers can delete accounts anytime.\nNightDrive may suspend accounts for violations or malicious activity.\nLiability, IP, and indemnification clauses survive termination.\n9. Modifications & Governing Law\nTerms may be updated; continued use = acceptance.\nGoverned by Romanian law, jurisdiction of Bucharest courts.\n10. Contact\nEmail: mihai.arisanu2006@gmail.com", 8);
